data.title: Danish Prime Minister on a Working Visit to the Czech Republic
data.meta_description: Danish Prime Minister on a Working Visit to the Czech Republic
data.text:
Tomorrow, on Saturday, March 24, 2007, Prime Minister Mirek Topolánek of the Czech Republic will receive Danish Premier Anders Fogh Rasmussen who will be on a working visit to the Czech Republic.

Their bilateral talks will focus primarily on economic co-operation between their two countries, the Berlin Declaration, the European Union’s energy policy, enlargement of the EU, free movement of labour, and the Czech Republic’s full integration in the Schengen system.

Programme:

11:25 a.m. - opening ceremony, photo opportunity, garden of the Office of the Government of the Czech Republic, nábøeží E. Beneše 4, Prague 1

11:45 a.m. - negotiations of the two delegations, Room No. 162, Office of the Government of the Czech Republic

2:00 p.m. - press conference, Hrzánský palác, Loretánská 177/9, Prague 1

Journalists are requested to arrive at least 20 minutes before the event.
